# Basic Approach
we create another function called generateBSTs which takes two parameters, the strart node value and the end node value
1. If the start node value is greater than the end node then add the null to the currentBST list and return it
2. for every node from start to end, make it as our root node value do
3. call generateBSTs to generate leftSubtree with start as current start and end as value before until current root value ,which returns the list of roots of unique left subtrees formed with values from start to currentroot value - 1 
4. call generateBSTs to generate rightSubtree with start as current currentrootvalue + 1 and end as current end ,which returns the list of roots of unique right subtrees formed with values from currentroot value + 1 to end
5. now to get all combinations of left subtrees and right subtrees for the current root, traverse using two for loops and create a root with value as current root value and add the leftchild and rightchild with the help of for loops
6. add the root node to the currentBST list
7. return the currentBST list 
# Code
```
class Solution {
    public List<TreeNode> generateTrees(int n) {
        return generateBSTs(1, n);
    }
    List<TreeNode> generateBSTs(int start, int end) {
        List<TreeNode> currentBSTs = new ArrayList<>();
        if(start > end) currentBSTs.add(null);        
        else {
            for(int rootVal = start; rootVal <= end; rootVal ++) {                
                List<TreeNode> leftSubtreeRoots = generateBSTs(start, rootVal - 1);
                List<TreeNode> rightSubtreeRoots = generateBSTs(rootVal + 1, end);
                for(TreeNode leftChild : leftSubtreeRoots) {                    
                    for(TreeNode rightChild : rightSubtreeRoots) {
                        TreeNode root = new TreeNode(rootVal);
                        root.left = leftChild;
                        root.right = rightChild;
                        currentBSTs.add(root);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        return currentBSTs;
    }
}
```

