EXPLANATION : -
Idea -  Median divides array into 2 equal parts.
We will make 2 heaps one max heap and one min heap. We will store first half of current elements in max heap (as top() function will return maximum value of first half) and min heap will store second half (as top() function will give minimum value of second half ) While inserting the new element if it is less than left.top() (max heap ) then we will insert it into left part else into right part. As to maintain size of both of the parts equal if the difference between both the parts is greater than 1 then we will exchange one element from larger part to smaller part.
For finding median : - if size of both parts is same then median = (left.top()+right.top())/2; else the top element of bigger part.

Note - ap function is just doing functionality of abs function.

